shared_text:
Governor Mike DeWine is sharing a COVID-19 Update.
July 22 at 5:50 PM ·

Governor DeWine announced that beginning on Thursday, July 23, at 6:00 p.m., a statewide mask mandate will go into effect for citizens living in all 88 Ohio counties.

With some exceptions, all individuals in Ohio will be required to wear a mask in public.

"Our preliminary data indicate that the rate of increase in new cases has slowed in the high-risk counties where masks are already mandated, so we are cautiously optimistic that things are heading in the right direction," said Governor DeWine. "We believe that requiring masks statewide will make a significant difference and will be key to making sure other counties do not progress to a higher level of increased spread."

More information: https://bit.ly/2D1kOVe

text: A Message from the GOAL Superintendent

post_text:
3/22/2020 Coronavirus Update 8:15 PM

This afternoon the state of Ohio issued a Stay at Home Order effective 11:59 p.m. on March 23, 2020, until 11:59 p.m. on April 6, 2020. You can view the full order here. As a result, we will
continue to operate as we have been while maintaining our top priority of keeping our families, students and staff safe. Students and families if you are struggling academically, emotionally or are worried about basic essentials please contact your educational advocate who will help you
connect to the resources that you need.

We understand that our students and GOAL families need guidance and expertise more than ever. GOAL Digital Academy is ready and committed to deliver. We will be sharing additional guidance regarding this order and other important legislative measures as information becomes available.

We are Community Strong and GOAL Strong,

Tish Jenkins
Superintendent

post_text:
Today, Governor Mike DeWine announced that he is ordering all schools in Ohio to close buildings for three weeks. The lab closure takes effect at the end of the school day on Monday, March 16, 2020. The Governor stated that he understands the impact that this will have on families, but the decision is necessary in order to slow down the community spread of coronavirus.

GOAL Digital Academy is working on clarification from the Department of Education as to whether students who attend an online school actually receive the extended break. Information will be quickly disseminated when we have clarifying answers.

What this means for our families and children is that students will attend school as scheduled on Friday, March 13, 2020, and Monday, March 16, 2020.
text:
Today, Governor Mike DeWine announced that he is ordering all schools in Ohio to close buildings for three weeks. The lab closure takes effect at the end of the school day on Monday, March 16, 2020. The Governor stated that he understands the impact that this will have on families, but the decision is necessary in order to slow down the community spread of coronavirus.

GOAL Digital Academy is working on clarification from the Department of Education as to whether students who attend an online school actually receive the extended break. Information will be quickly disseminated when we have clarifying answers.

What this means for our families and children is that students will attend school as scheduled on Friday, March 13, 2020, and Monday, March 16, 2020.

post_text:
GDA & Jobs for Ohio's Graduates students completed a 3 hour scavenger hunt around beautiful downtown Delaware for their Leadership Development Conference last week!

Students from surrounding counties visited 8 well known sites around the city including Ohio Wesleyan University, The Strand Theatre, Bun's Restaurant & Arch, Delaware County Department of Job & Family Services, St. Mary's Catholic Church (Delaware, Ohio), numerous monuments & Delaware County District Library!

We finished up the day Mingo Park with a wrap up & lunch provided by local favorite, The Backstretch Kitchen & Drinks.

Great job GOAL & JOG Students! Thank you to all of our local partners that could make this event a successful leadership opportunity for students in our area! :)

post_text:
100 years ago on this day, the 11th day of the 11th month, at the 11th hour, Germany signs an armistice agreement bringing an end to The Great War or World War I.
Today we remember the veterans of this war who have now all passed on from the face of the Earth, the last being Florence Green, a British soldier who died in February of 2012 at the age of 110.
Nearly 10 million military deaths were reported in this war, making it one of the bloodiest wars in human history behind only the Mongol Conquests of the 13th century and World War II.
